-- China to Build 300 MW Wind Farm Off Hebei Coast, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2012-01-13T15:44:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/china-to-build-300-mw-wind-farm-off-hebei-coast-xinhua-reports.html
China will build a 300 megawatt wind
farm off the coast of Leting county in the northern province of
Hebei, Xinhua News Agency reported, citing a feasibility report
from the National Energy Bureau.  The 5.76 billion yuan ($913 million) project will receive
all required government approvals by year-end and will be
connected to the  power grid  by the end of 2015, the official
news service repported.  The farm, an array of 100 units of 3 MW offshore turbines,
will generate 752 million kilowatt hours of power and 730
million yuan in sales annually, Xinhua said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  